## 2026-07-07 - Orca comparative study: verified adoption backlog + 5 real bugs found (Fable/Claude)

- A 32-agent workflow study (`wf_63e2b54a-2b8`) compared stablyai/orca
  (Electron parallel-agent IDE, ~1.4M LoC TS) against Engram. All 12 migration
  candidates were adversarially verified against both repos; the security
  subsystem read was delegated to Codex CLI after Sonnet safety-filter false
  positives on ai-vault/credential code.
- Real Engram bugs found during verification (unfixed as of 2026-07-07):
  (1) `EngramServiceReadProvider.sourceFailedIndexJobCounts()` (~L1479)
  filters `status IN ('failed_retryable','failed_terminal','failed')` but
  `IndexJobRunner` only writes `'failed_permanent'` — permanent failures are
  undercounted in per-source health. (2) SEC-C2 `validateProjectPathConfined`
  allows `src == $HOME`/`dst == $HOME` exactly and has no
  ancestor-of-tracked-project check. (3) `ObservabilityRetention.swift` prunes
  tables the runtime no longer writes (per `OSLogReader.swift` comment) — dead
  maintenance code kept alive by its own tests. (4) Dead settings keys
  (`syncNodeName`, `syncEnabled`, embedding fields) read as live features.
  (5) `generate_summary` error path rethrows raw URLSession errors unwrapped
  and discards `EngramServiceError.retryPolicy`/`name` before the UI.
- Verified top adoption items: SQLite backup ring via periodic `VACUUM INTO`
  (insights/manual links/favorites/migration_log have zero snapshot insurance;
  UndoMigration error text references a backup that does not exist);
  `SessionCostPricing` hardening (11 stale models, no aliases/tiers,
  unmatched → $0; port shape from orca claude-usage + codex-usage;
  `backfillCosts` only recomputes cost=0 rows); wire the 3 dormant boundary
  scripts (`check-app-mcp-cli-direct-writes.sh` etc.) into CI plus run
  bundle-hygiene on PRs (currently tag-only); MCP tool docs — add
  per-error-code recovery guidance + read-tool selection boundaries (search
  degradation warning and project_move sequencing docs already exist; gap is
  narrower than first claimed); typed near-tie "ambiguous" state for Layer-2
  parent suggestions; stale-but-useful status retention for HomeView Service
  State + PopoverView Live section; source staleness concept for SourcePulse
  healthStatus.
- Rejected by verification (do NOT re-propose): cold-restore marker
  (`file_index_state` mtime+inode+device already covers it); byte-offset
  incremental indexing framed as new (it is deferred internal backlog #19 with
  `parsed_offset`/`boundary_hash` columns already in schema); SwiftUI error
  boundaries (Swift traps are uncatchable; WorkGraphView do/catch pattern +
  zero force-unwraps already cover the catchable subset); protected-path
  denylist as net-new (SEC-C2 exists with tests — only the $HOME-equality
  loophole remains).
- Strategic conclusion: Orca's own
  `docs/reference/reliability-pain-points-2026-06-30.md` (9 open P0, 191 open
  P1, 386 PRs/week, JSON-store regression #5356) is primary evidence FOR
  Engram's passive-observer + Swift-owned-SQLite boundary. Never adopt: live
  OAuth quota calls, agent-driving, mobile relay stack, JSON primary store,
  product CLI, i18n backend.

