## 2026-07-06 - Stale screenshot baselines: check provenance before trusting SSIM failures (Fable/Claude)

- PR #103 (feature-cut ITEM 0) blocked on `settings_dark` SSIM=0.8982 vs the
  0.91 threshold. Root cause was NOT a regression: the checked-in baseline
  (`macos/EngramUITests/baselines/settings_dark.png`, git-LFS) dated from
  322f5095 — a Chinese-locale capture predating the forced
  `-AppleLanguages (en)` in `TestLaunchConfig`, still showing deleted Web UI
  rows. It only ever passed marginally (0.9157 on the last green main run);
  a legitimate UI change tipped it over. Fixed in 12c70690 by refreshing the
  baseline from the CI `screenshot-diffs-full` artifact (top-level PNGs are
  the actual captures; `diffs/` holds the diff overlays).
- How to apply: before treating a screenshot-compare failure as a product
  regression, `git log` + view the baseline — if it predates en-localization
  or shows deleted UI, refresh it from the CI artifact instead of patching
  the UI. Follow-up resolved in PR #113: `settings_page` and
  `settings_general` were refreshed from the same CI actual-capture source, and
  `settings_network` is no longer a tracked baseline or active screenshot
  capture in current main.
- Related flake: `ui-test-smoke` has job `timeout-minutes: 10`
  (.github/workflows/test.yml:178); a cold-cache build (~6 min) plus tests
  (~4 min) can blow it — the canceled step still shows 0 test failures and
  screenshot compare passes afterwards. Rerun before diagnosing; consider
  bumping to 15 if it recurs.

## 2026-07-05 - Preference: route fan-out subagents to sonnet/opus, not Fable (Fable/Claude)

- User feedback ("你全都派Fable啊?") when 8 PR-review finder agents all
  default-inherited Fable: do NOT let fan-out subagents inherit the top-tier
  main-loop model.
- How to apply: set `model: 'sonnet'` for mechanical scan/verify stages and
  `model: 'opus'` for judgment-heavy propose/synthesize stages explicitly on
  Agent / workflow agent() calls; reserve Fable for the single final
  adjudication step or main-loop reasoning. Reference pattern: the accepted
  2026-07-05 feature-cut workflow (sonnet mappers/verifiers, opus
  proposers/judge).

## 2026-07-05 - Menu-bar popover root cause: unbounded Live section and subagent churn (Fable/Claude)

- User-visible symptom: the menu-bar popover still felt overlong/low-signal after
  the earlier simplification and timeline cap. The final accepted root cause was
  NOT generic first-open latency: `PopoverView.liveSection` rendered all
  `liveSessions`, while `FileSystemEngramServiceReadProvider.liveSessions()`
  could return the service cap of 100 recent sessions. Runtime evidence in the
  Claude/Fable workflow found the set was dominated by Claude Code
  `/subagents/workflows/*.jsonl` churn and stale 15min-24h `recent` sessions.
- Final code shape:
  - `macos/Engram/Views/PopoverView.swift`: stable min box
    `.frame(minWidth: 400, maxWidth: 400, minHeight: 420, alignment: .top)`,
    footer `Spacer(minLength: 0)`, `visibleLiveSessions` filters to
    `activityLevel == "active" || "idle"`, renders
    `visible.prefix(Self.liveSectionLimit)` with `liveSectionLimit = 5`, and
    uses `popover_liveOverflow` for the remaining count.
  - `macos/EngramService/Core/EngramServiceReadProvider.swift`:
    `considerLiveSessionCandidate` excludes files whose path components contain
    `subagents`, keeping subagent transcript churn out of the live scan.
  - `macos/Engram/Views/Settings/GeneralSettingsSection.swift` and
    `macos/Engram/MenuBarController.swift`: `showMenuBarActivity` lets the user
    keep the menu-bar icon static while still surfacing hard service failures.
- Verification recorded by Fable/Claude in `CHANGELOG.md`: source-inspection
  `HomePopoverActionsTests` for stable height/live cap/overflow/menu-bar toggle,
  real temp-dir `EngramServiceIPCTests.testFileSystemProviderExcludesSubagentChurnFromLiveScan`,
  Debug build, Release/local deploy, and installed-binary marker
  `popover_liveOverflow`. Codex doc-sync spot check on 2026-07-05 also found
  `popover_liveOverflow` and `Show Activity in Menu Bar` in
  `/Applications/Engram.app`.
- Current user state: user said Fable found the root cause and the result is now
  satisfactory. Future agents should preserve this as the accepted explanation
  unless fresh runtime evidence contradicts it.

## 2026-07-03 - Perf audit implemented as 8 reviewed PRs #95-#102 (Claude)

- Same-day follow-up to the audit entry below: all 25 confirmed findings (minus
  explicit deferrals) implemented via a 21-agent workflow (opus implement →
  adversarial review → fix, 8 parallel worktree implementers) + a 3-agent
  closeout. All 8 PRs reached zero-blocking review verdicts. At Claude handoff,
  PRs were OPEN, not merged. See CHANGELOG.md [Unreleased] for the full per-PR
  breakdown and Codex deployment closeout.
  - #98 search fallback CTE; #96 startup gating x4; #97 UI hotpath x4;
    #99 service read/render x4; #95 MCP dense paging (contract preserved);
    #102 indexer parse-once + skip short-circuit; #100 adapter windowed reads
    x3; #101 fts_map incremental FTS (structural).
- Codex follow-up on 2026-07-04 integrated all eight PR branches locally into
  `codex/perf-integration-review`, reviewed them as a combined change, and fixed
  three verified issues before deployment:
  - Startup skip-tier cleanup now deletes and counts stale `fts_map` rows in
    addition to `sessions_fts` and embeddings (`StartupBackfills` +
    `StartupBackfillTests`).
