- CI GOTCHA (cost 3 follow-up commits): the repo TRACKS
  macos/Engram.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj and CI's swift-unit job runs
  `xcodegen generate` + diff as a drift check. Rules: (1) when adding Swift
  files you MUST commit the regenerated pbxproj; (2) xcodegen embeds the ROOT
  DIRECTORY NAME as the top-level group name, so regenerating inside a git
  worktree with a nonstandard name leaks that name into pbxproj — always
  regenerate from a directory literally named `engram`; (3) a sed rename is NOT
  enough (stale deterministic UUIDs still drift) — regenerate, don't patch.
