## 2026-06-27 - Session implementation digest and work timeline first pass (Codex)

- Implemented the first deterministic "what work happened" layer for sessions.
  The indexer now extracts `SessionImplementationBeat` values from real user
  turns plus the strongest completion-style assistant report, ignoring machine
  instructions, AGENTS/bootstrap text, tool results, local-command wrappers, and
  progress chatter unless they are operation evidence.
- New schema table: `session_work_beats` keyed by `(session_id, beat_index)`,
  with action date/timestamp, work key/title, human intent, assistant outcome,
  kind, status, operation events, and confidence. Snapshot writes replace beats
  on healthy re-streams and preserve existing beats on empty failed re-streams.
- Existing reliable historical sessions can be backfilled by
  `EngramDatabaseIndexer.indexImplementationBeatBackfillSessions`; startup runs
  that backfill after instruction backfill and before normal initial indexing.
- Timeline read surface: `DatabaseManager.implementationTimeline(...)` reads
  stored beats, applies normal visibility/project/date filters, drops
  operation-only beats, and uses `ImplementationTimelineBuilder` to merge
  adjacent same-work dates while splitting later non-contiguous returns into
  later batches.
- App UI: Timeline now has a Work/Sessions segmented mode. Work mode shows
  grouped work rows with date ranges, batch labels, source session count,
  status/kind, and extracted human intent / assistant outcome.
- Planning artifact: `docs/superpowers/plans/2026-06-27-session-implementation-timeline.md`.
