## 2026-06-26 - P1 c.1+c.2: semantic memory foundation (embedding client, KNN, RRF, schema) shipped & verified (Claude)

- KEY ARCHITECTURE DECISION: semantic memory uses **pure-Swift brute-force cosine KNN over Float32
  BLOBs, NOT sqlite-vec** — no native dependency, no build-system risk, fully unit-testable; fast
  enough for a local personal corpus (optionally FTS/project pre-filtered). Provider is
  OpenAI-compatible (configurable baseURL — SiliconFlow/DashScope/DeepSeek/OpenAI), default embedding
  `text-embedding-3-small`, all opt-in (empty key → keyword fallback).
- c.1 (`macos/Shared/EngramCore/AI/`, public in EngramCoreRead, also compiled into EngramMCP via
  `path: Shared`): `OpenAICompatibleEmbeddingClient` (URLSession-injectable, L2-normalized,
  order-preserving), `SessionChunker` (port of chunker.ts), `VectorMath` (normalize/cosine/dot +
  LE-Float32 BLOB encode/decode).
- c.2: `VectorSearch.knn` (brute-force cosine top-K) + `RankFusion.rrf` (Reciprocal Rank Fusion,
  deterministic tie-break) — pure, tested. Schema adds `insight_embeddings`, `semantic_chunks`,
  `embedding_meta` (CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS in baseline, no version bump). Renamed from
  `session_chunks` to `semantic_chunks` to avoid colliding with the legacy TS-reference vector tables
  (`session_chunks`/`session_embeddings`) that `VectorRebuildPolicy` clears.
- Module placement note: `Shared/EngramCore` is compiled by EngramCoreRead (framework, public types →
  EngramCoreWrite/Service import it) AND directly by EngramMCP (tool, `path: Shared`). New files need
  `xcodegen generate`.
- Verified: EngramCoreTests 494/494 (SemanticMemoryUnitTests 10 + testSemanticMemoryTablesCreated).
- REMAINING for c (c.3): config reader (settings/keychain → EmbeddingConfig); service embedding write
  job (embed insights/sessions → BLOB tables) + d's deferred supersession/access writes;
  `get_memory`/`search` hybrid wiring (embed query → KNN → RRF + lifecycle); re-enable
  `semantic`/`hybrid` modes when provider+embeddings present; localhost-mock-server e2e. Then f
  (corpus mining). MCPDatabase lives in the EngramMCP executable (tested only via spawned stdio), so
  the e2e semantic path needs a localhost mock embeddings server.

