## 2026-06-21 - Multi-Mac sync L2: PR #88 non-security review remediation

The prior session (`0d64bab9`) ran the pre-merge review workflow `wlqv61o7n`
(verdict `fix-before-merge`: 2 must-fix HIGH + 12 followups) but **derailed on
the security dimension** — the Opus cyber-safety filter killed both the
`review:security` agent and the main turn that re-read the security-findings
page — so it shipped no fixes. This session collected every NON-security finding
and completed them (commit `0fe2a4cd` on `feat/multimac-session-sync`), then
adversarially re-verified each with an 8-agent workflow.

LESSON (recurring): on this repo's remote-sync/server code the security review
dimension reliably trips the cyber-safety filter. Action the non-security
dimensions; delegate security to a subagent and read only a short digest, never
the raw findings page. Owner scopes security out ("安全的不用补了").

Fixes (see `CHANGELOG.md` for the full list):
- HIGH: `pushProject` read-merges the per-peer manifest (was full-replace →
  pushing a 2nd project dropped the 1st from discovery), fail-closed on
  GET/decode error; `pushCandidates` excludes already-offloaded sessions (was
  republishing the collapsed FTS shadow + overwriting the rehydrate key).
- MED/LOW/NIT: blank-cwd over-match guard (`? <> '' AND cwd = ?`); published
  entry `project` normalized to the requested name (cwd-only sessions now
  importable); `content_hash IS NOT NULL` guard; `agent_role` defense-in-depth;
  preview `SessionPreview.id` carries the real id; `ManifestCodec.isManifestKey`
  symmetric catalog filtering (rejects `..`).
- Deliberately NOT changed: `publishedManifestEntries` keeps no offload_state
  guard — it JOINs the 'out' ledger (chokepoint already excludes subagents), and
  guarding it would drop a legitimately-pushed-then-offloaded session.
- Tests: +10 RemoteSync tests (incl. fail-closed manifest w/ a failure-injection
  backend). SessionSyncTests 14/14, EngramServiceCore RemoteSync 11/11,
  EngramRemoteServerCore 9/9, full Engram build SUCCEEDED.
- NOT merged: PR #88 still open; new commit re-triggers CI. Stale worktrees from
  prior sessions (`.worktrees/full-review-remediation-impl` etc.) left untouched.

## 2026-06-21 - Multi-Mac sync: L1 Unison files live + L2 server catalog shipped

- Goal (owner): iCloud-like but MANUAL+CONFIRMED multi-Mac sync via the macmini-hub
  (`macmini-hq`, ssh bing@10.0.10.100, tailnet 100.125.101.60). Each owner Mac
  push/pulls a project's FILES + AI SESSION RECORDS through the hub, on demand, with a
  diff preview + single confirm; transfer P2P over tailnet. Builds on the offload
  foundation in [[2026-06-20 - Plain-HTTP-over-Tailscale offload + second server macmini-hq live]].
- Two layers: L1 = Unison bidirectional FILE sync; L2 = Engram cross-machine
  SESSION-RECORD sync. Designed via `multimac-sync-design` workflow (run wc092o7ys),
  then REVIEWED by the Codex subagent (verdict: architecture sound; 4 HIGH impl traps).
- L1 (files) DONE+validated, pilot ReadOut: copied the dev Mac's Unison 2.54.0 binary to
  `/Users/bing/bin/unison` on the mini (otool dep=libSystem only → no Homebrew/source
  build; chmod+codesign -s -; version BYTE-MATCHES, mandatory for Unison). Profiles
  `~/.unison/readout.prf` (+`readout-claude.prf`) over ssh-on-tailnet; ignore
  Readout.app/.DS_Store/.codegraph/VCS. Wrapper `~/bin/engram-sync push|pull <proj>`:
  read-only preview via `printf '' | unison <prf> -terse` (EOF-aborts before applying —
  EMPIRICALLY verified zero writes) → single confirm → `-batch -force <dir>` (force
  target derived per-profile: local root on push, ssh root on pull). Conflict safety
  verified: two-sided edit → reported + SKIPPED, never overwritten. Hub canonical root
  `~/sync/<proj>` is staging only, never an AI cwd. NOTE: ReadOut's claude dir has NO
  *.jsonl (only a memory file) — those 28 claude sessions' transcripts aren't co-located,
  which is why L2 (transcript via Engram record) is the right channel, not L1 file sync.
- L2 server catalog DONE+deployed+tested: `BlobStore.listKeys(prefix:)` +
  bearer-gated `GET /v1/catalog` aggregating per-peer `catalog.<peer>.manifest` blobs →
  `{schemaVersion,manifests:[...]}` (server stays format-agnostic; corrupt manifests
  skipped). `EngramRemoteBackend.catalog()`. EngramRemoteServerCore tests 9/9. Rebuilt
  + redeployed the server bundle to the mini; verified live (auth→empty manifests,
  no-auth→401, offload unaffected).
- L2 CLIENT now DONE + deployed + LIVE-verified (2026-06-21, second pass). Built via workflow
  (implement->review->harden; harden+security stages died on API errors so I finished/reconciled
  by hand). NO-MIGRATION design: import state on existing sessions cols (origin/authoritative_node
  =peer, snapshot_hash=bundle hash dedup), deterministic id remote:<peer>:<sid>, SQLite UPSERT (not
  REPLACE). v1 bundle reused (no hash break). publishOnlyCommit writes a sync_ledger 'out' row WITHOUT
  collapsing local FTS. push only local-origin sessions (no echo). New: ManifestCodec, ImportRepo,
  OffloadRepo.{publishOnlyCommit,pushCandidates,publishedManifestEntries}, RemoteSyncCoordinator.
  {pushProject,pullProject,previewProjectSync}, IPC remoteProjectSyncPreview(read-only)/
  remotePushProject/remotePullProject (last two in ServiceCapabilityToken.protectedCommands).
  Tests green across EngramCore/EngramServiceCore/EngramRemoteServerCore (push->pull round-trip,
  preview read-only, pull-skips-own-manifest). LIVE on ReadOut: pushed 2 top-level sessions ->
  /v1/catalog shows them -> re-preview toPush 0 (idempotent); simulated foreign-peer manifest
  pulled -> imported 1 searchable row origin=peer, own manifest skipped. Wrapper engram-sync does
  combined L1+L2 preview behind one confirm. Remaining enhancement (non-blocking): schema-v2 bundle
  with rendered transcript for full role-tagged replay of imported sessions (today: searchable +
  summary + metadata; transcript view falls back to FTS).
- (historical, superseded above) L2 client was initially deferred. Original remaining list:
  ManifestCodec (manifest from sync_ledger 'out' rows); publishOnlyCommit
  (push writes ledger row WITHOUT collapsing local FTS — current commitOffloaded
  clobbers, OffloadRepo.swift:193); ImportRepo.commitImported (INSERT-only foreign row
  `remote:<peer>:<sid>` + FTS + ledger direction='import'); idempotent sync_ledger
  table-rebuild migration to extend the direction CHECK (currently IN('out','in'),
  EngramMigrations ~:420) to add 'import'; IPC remotePushProject/remotePullProject/
  remoteProjectCatalog + DTOs + EngramServiceClient/protocol/mock; add the mutating
  push/pull to ServiceCapabilityToken.protectedCommands; wrapper L2 hook.
