## 2026-06-10 - Multi-expert audit (security dimension excluded)

- Full-repo read-only audit: 11 domain experts + adversarial verification
  (272 subagents, two passes; first pass hit the monthly spend limit and was
  resumed from the workflow journal).
- Results: 88 confirmed findings (26 high / 50 medium / 12 low, 0 critical),
  9 refuted, 1 disputed, 8 UNVERIFIED carryovers (lost to the interruption,
  e.g. stale SessionCostPricing table -> cost_usd=0 for current models).
- Report: `docs/reviews/2026-06-10-multi-expert-audit.md`; summary in CHANGELOG.md [Unreleased].
  Hotspots: EngramService/Core, EngramCoreWrite/Indexing, Engram/Views.
- Systemic themes: per-view ad-hoc ISO8601 parsing; 30s IPC frame deadline vs
  long commands; sessions_fts.session_id UNINDEXED full scans; AI generation
  pipeline inert in default config; resume/launch surface broken end-to-end;
  tests that cannot fail (source-string asserts, TS-generated fixture DB).
- STANDING USER PREFERENCE: do NOT include a security/vulnerability expert in
  multi-agent reviews of this repo (risk-control false triggers); state "no
  security analysis" in reviewer prompts. No findings fixed as of 2026-06-10.

