## 2026-06-06 — Codex project-move compatibility verification (Codex)

Codex verified the Codex project-move surface after the Claude/Qoder directory
encoding fix.

Conclusion:
- Codex does not use Claude-style cwd-encoded project directories. Active
  sessions live under `.codex/sessions`; archived sessions live under
  `.codex/archived_sessions`.
- TypeScript `src/core/project-move/sources.ts` and Swift
  `macos/EngramCoreWrite/ProjectMove/Sources.swift` both register `codex` and
  `codex-archived` as flat roots with no `encodeProjectDir`, so project move
  scans and patches literal path references in JSONL content but does not
  rename Codex directories.
- The Swift `CodexAdapter` also expands `.codex/sessions` to include
  `.codex/archived_sessions`.

Evidence:
- Read-only local corpus scan found 2,175 Codex rollout JSONL files, 2,165
  cwd-bearing sessions, zero non-absolute cwd values, and zero project-dir-like
  path layouts. Five archived sessions live directly under
  `.codex/archived_sessions`, which is still covered by the flat archived root.

Verification:
- `npx vitest run tests/core/project-move/sources.test.ts
  tests/core/project-move/orchestrator.integration.test.ts
  tests/core/project-move/review.test.ts` passed 50 tests.
- `xcodebuild test -project macos/Engram.xcodeproj -scheme EngramCoreTests
  -destination 'platform=macOS'
  -only-testing:EngramCoreTests/SessionSourcesTests/testRootsReturnsCanonicalRootsInOrder
  -only-testing:EngramCoreTests/SessionSourcesTests/testEncodeProjectDirSetForGroupedSourcesOnly
  -only-testing:EngramCoreTests/OrchestratorTests/testCodexArchivedSessionsArePatchedAndCommitted
  -only-testing:EngramCoreTests/ReviewScanTests CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=NO`
  passed 10 tests.

## 2026-06-06 — TypeScript empty-reindex session fact preservation (Codex)

Codex closed a TS/Swift parity gap where an empty or degraded re-parse could
erase known-good session facts in the TypeScript reference layer.

Change:
- `src/core/session-merge.ts` now preserves the existing `cwd` when a newer
  authoritative snapshot has an empty cwd.
- The same merge path preserves the existing message-count breakdown when the
  incoming snapshot reports zero total messages and the current snapshot already
  has messages.
- `src/core/db/session-repo.ts` applies the same preservation rule in both
  `upsertSession` and `upsertAuthoritativeSnapshot` conflict updates, so direct
  database writes cannot clobber those known-good facts.
- Direct authoritative upsert also preserves the existing `quality_score` under
  the same empty-reindex predicate, keeping the derived score aligned with the
  preserved counts.

Verification:
