## 2026-06-05 — Claude Code dir-encoding compat fix (Claude)

Real Claude Code project-dir rule = replace EVERY char not in `[A-Za-z0-9]`
with `-` (`s.replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9]/g,"-")`, per UTF-16 unit, no collapse/case).
Engram's Swift `ClaudeCodeProjectDir.encode` only did `/`+`.` → broke 9/39 real
dirs (projects with `_`/space); TS `encodeCC` only did `/`. Fixed both + tests.

Why it mattered: wrong dir name → orchestrator `rename` ENOENT → silently
`skippedDirs(.missing)` → real session dir never renamed → Claude Code can't see
migrated history (Engram's content index still showed it, masking the bug). The
bug was enshrined in unit tests (`john_doe`→`john_doe`, `my proj`→`my proj`).

Verified: 39/39 real CC dirs + 7/7 qoder dirs follow the all-non-alnum rule;
undo/recover are path-derived (recompute encode) so the fix is reverse-safe;
ProjectMove tests 86/86 + encoder 10/10 + TS 9/9.

Reusable audit method (Codex side): per dir, read first file's `cwd`, assert
`basename(dir) == adapter.encode(cwd)`; mismatch = encoder wrong. Dir names
start with `-` → prefix `./` for find/grep. Reconcile for already-orphaned dirs
designed but deferred (no real orphans on this machine yet). Details in
CHANGELOG.md "Claude Code project-migration encoder fix".

Closeout update (2026-06-06, Codex): the handoff items above are resolved except
for the intentionally deferred reconcile feature. Codex flat-layout coverage is
closed by the active+archived Codex migration tests; Gemini/iFlow grouped-source
coverage is closed by the compatibility follow-up; the Claude/qoder encoder fix
was pushed and merged via PR #51 (`485b932b`), and the MCP-only residual helper
was fixed via PR #52 (`f8180379`). Reconcile for already-orphaned historical dirs
remains deferred because the real-disk audit found no local orphan to repair.

