## 2026-06-04 — TypeScript FTS table-swap rebuild PR (Codex)

Branch/worktree: `feat/fts-table-swap-rebuild` at
`.worktrees/fts-table-swap-rebuild`; started from `origin/main` after PR #37
merged as `5cccdd5b`.

Implemented:
- Added `src/core/db/fts-rebuild-policy.ts` to own TypeScript `FTS_VERSION`,
  rebuild metadata, `sessions_fts_rebuild` shadow-table setup, copied active FTS
  rows, dual-write/delete helpers, and transactional final swap.
- Changed TypeScript migration from direct FTS-version completion to an online
  pending rebuild: active `sessions_fts` remains the search source, shadow rows
  are copied once, completed FTS jobs reopen, vector tables clear, and empty DBs
  mark the current version without a pending rebuild.
- Routed `replaceFtsContent`, `indexSessionContent`, `deleteIndexArtifacts`,
  `deleteSession`, and subagent FTS maintenance cleanup through rebuild-aware
  helpers while keeping active reads on `sessions_fts`.
- Exposed `Database.finalizeFtsRebuildIfReady()` and made `IndexJobRunner`
  attempt finalization after each FTS job completion path.
- Addressed follow-up review findings before PR: pending shadow tables now must
  match the expected FTS5/trigram schema before reuse/final swap, stale or
  non-FTS `sessions_fts_rebuild` tables are recreated from active rows, and
  `deleteIndexArtifacts`/`deleteSession` attempt finalization after draining the
  last recoverable FTS job.

