## 2026-06-04 — Additional non-blocking follow-up remediation (Codex)

Branch/worktree: `followups/full-remediation` at
`.worktrees/followups-full-remediation`; continuing PR #34.

Implemented after the first closeout because the remaining items were
non-blocking but still useful:
- CI runtime hygiene: GitHub Actions workflows now set
  `FORCE_JAVASCRIPT_ACTIONS_TO_NODE24=true` so third-party JavaScript actions
  opt into the Node 24 runtime before GitHub's Node 20 deprecation cutoff.
  Existing actionlint ShellCheck warnings in screenshot-copy shell snippets were
  fixed by quoting the screenshots directory variable.
- TS duration helper cleanup: `durationMinutes` is shared through
  `src/core/time.ts`, and both session scoring and tiering use the same
  finite-number guard for invalid timestamps.
- TS FTS version refresh safety: FTS version refresh no longer deletes
  `sessions_fts` up front. Existing keyword search rows remain live while
  `size_bytes = 0` drives the indexer refresh, avoiding a temporary empty-search
  window during version upgrades.
- Swift MCP cancellation: stdio `tools/call` requests with ids now run as
  in-flight tasks, `notifications/cancelled` cancels matching string or numeric
  request ids, stdout writes are serialized, EOF waits for in-flight responses,
  and cancellation returns structured MCP tool errors with
  `structuredContent.code = "cancelled"`.
- Swift socket cancellation: `UnixSocketEngramServiceTransport` still uses
  fd shutdown to break blocking read/write, but now normalizes post-cancel I/O
  failures into `CancellationError` so stdio cancellation does not degrade into
  `serviceUnavailable`.

