## 2026-06-04 — Follow-up remediation branch closeout (Codex)

Branch/worktree: `followups/full-remediation` at
`.worktrees/followups-full-remediation`.

Implemented after the 2026-06-03 review remediation set:
- Swift MCP/Service transcript safety: introduced a shared
  `TranscriptSizeGuard` and wired it through MCP transcript reads and Service
  exports so oversized Gemini JSON transcripts fail before full-file loading,
  with structured MCP/service errors and regression tests.
- Swift secret flow: `EngramServiceLauncher` no longer injects Keychain-derived
  API keys through child-process environment variables. The service resolves
  `@keychain` settings directly through Keychain, ignores legacy
  `ENGRAM_KEYCHAIN_*` environment fallbacks, and launcher tests assert the
  service environment is scrubbed.
- Swift MCP `get_context`: full-detail context now includes SQLite-backed
  operational signals for dirty/unpushed git repos, 7-day file hotspots, and
  recent 24h errors. Live sessions and background alerts remain unavailable to
  the standalone Swift MCP process because those are daemon in-memory signals.
- CLI/test coverage: `resume.ts` now has an import-safe direct-execution guard
  plus exported pure helpers; the CLI dispatcher explicitly invokes
  `resume.main`; `project` flag parsing and resume filtering/command display
  have Vitest coverage.
- Tool/web correctness: `list_sessions.total` now reports total matching rows
  instead of current page length, with `since/until` propagated through
  `countSessions`; search route failure warnings no longer echo internal
  exception text.
- Test isolation: `testFormerBridgeCommandsUseNativeServiceBehavior` now uses
  `ServiceCoreTestHomeScope` so local user AI settings cannot force real LLM
  calls during ServiceCore tests.

