## 2026-05-30 — deferred follow-ups closed and local app deployed (Codex)

Resumed from Claude session `93d5af5d-80b5-42ee-bca2-b397732c0dd0` and chose
the bundled continuation scope the user requested: include the two deferred
items plus all follow-ups instead of only counting them.

Closed deferred items:
- **mig-2**: `FTSRebuildPolicy` now builds `sessions_fts_rebuild` as a shadow
  table, keeps the live `sessions_fts` searchable while rebuild jobs run, and
  atomically swaps the shadow into place only after recoverable FTS jobs drain.
  Fresh empty databases mark `fts_version=3` immediately so parity/fresh-schema
  checks still see current metadata.
- **conc-1**: `UnixSocketServiceServer` now offloads blocking frame read/write
  calls to a dedicated concurrent GCD queue, keeping per-client socket I/O off
  Swift's cooperative executor while preserving #32's socket-timeout behavior.

Closed follow-ups:
- CI `swift-unit` now runs `Engram`, `EngramServiceCore`, and `EngramMCPTests`,
  so service-core and MCP regressions are no longer only compile-gated.
- Post-push CI exposed that `mcp-contract.sqlite` stores an absolute transcript
  path from the fixture-generation machine. `testGetSessionMatchesGolden` now
  copies the fixture DB and rewrites `mcp-transcript-01.file_path` to the current
